detaileddescription.para: When a derived argument structure is defined for an instrument, this method should be overridden to fill it. This is mandatory in case a pricing engine is used.
When a derived result structure is defined for an instrument, this method should be overridden to read from it. This is mandatory in case a pricing engine is used.
This method must leave the instrument in a consistent state when the expiration condition is met.
This throws if the nominal is not constant across coupons.
This throws if the nominals are not the same for the two legs.

memberdef.name: FixedVsFloatingSwap

detaileddescription.para: If no payment convention is passed, the convention of the floating-rate schedule is used.

simplesect.para: if Settings::includeReferenceDateCashFlows() is set to true, payments occurring at the settlement date of the swap might be included in the NPV and therefore affect the fair-rate and fair-spread calculation. This might not be what you want.
